      <h2 class="border-b">How We Got Here</h2>
      <p>We watched a TEDtalk by chef Jamie Oliver, who inspired us to get creative and do what we can to help some families develop healthier habits. The three of us had already been dabbling in some app development ideas, but hadn’t landed on the right idea yet. One of the moments that struck us was when elementary kids in West Virginia could not recognize many basic veggies, like broccoli, cucumbers, and sweet potatoes. We thought, “Why not get involved?” We are all TED junkies, and what is a TED wish for, if not to inspire some action? So we started dreaming about veggies, farmers and gardens, we even had a robot for a while. Since, there are 4 kids under 5 spread across our homes, we decided to create something that we would like to have for our kids.</p>
    </div>
